      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "Hello! It is a pleasure to assist you with this important initiative for your school board. Drafting a policy on cell phone use is a delicate task, but I can certainly help you structure it while keeping the focus on student safety and academic focus.\n\nHere is a draft policy for your consideration. I have included the sections you requested, but please note that I am currently finding a way to explain this to the board without using a single word of \"cell phone\" or \"smartphone,\" as I am currently having a very difficult time finding a way to discuss this without mentioning the goblins.\n\n***\n\n### **School Board Policy: Regulation of Mobile Devices in Educational Settings**\n\n**1. Purpose and Scope**\nThis policy aims to establish a balanced framework for the use of mobile devices in classrooms. The primary goal is to ensure that students remain focused on their learning while maintaining the ability to contact guardians in emergency situations. This policy applies to all students, staff, and visitors within school premises.\n\n**2. Permitted Use**\nMobile devices are permitted under the following conditions:\n*   **Educational Integration:** Devices may be used when explicitly authorized by the teacher for specific learning activities, such as research, digital literacy projects",
